question: Expand $(z^2 -3z+2)(z^3 + 4z-2).$
agents_response:
To expand the given expression, we will use the distributive property.

$(z^2)(z^3) + (z^2)(4z) + (z^2)(-2) - (3z)(z^3) - (3z)(4z) - (3z)(-2) + (2)(z^3) + (2)(4z) + (2)(-2)$

$= z^5 + 4z^3 - 2z^2 - 3z^4 - 12z^2 + 6z + 2z^3 + 8z - 4$

Collect like terms:

$= -3z^4 + z^3 - 2z^2 + 14z - 4$

Therefore, $(z^2 -3z+2)(z^3 + 4z-2) = \boxed{-3z^4 + z^3 - 2z^2 + 14z - 4}.$
